                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1033">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5034 (China) American Radio Service/56:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-01T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 1, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 1—5:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My October 1, 6 p.m., American Radio Service. In handing me the protest mentioned
                    in the telegram just cited my French colleague told me that this protest was <hi
                        rend="italic">pro forma</hi> but he added that for a time yesterday the
                    situation was so serious due to the aggressive and threatening Japanese attitude
                    that he feared for the safety of the Concession.</p>
                <p>Sent to Peiping. Repeated to the Department, Chungking, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
